{
  "texts": [
    "See a sample subset of these queries in Appendix B.Derived from this task domain, we select five specific preference dimensions described in Table 1cost, ambiance, age, time, and culture.",
    "Each dimension has bi-directional traits (e.g.",
    "luxury and budget for the dimension of cost), which corresponds with the positive and negative directions of the steering vector.",
    "In other words, to steer an LLM towards budget preferences, inject the cost steering vector 𝑣 𝑐𝑜𝑠𝑡 with a negative strength factor 𝑑 𝑐𝑜𝑠𝑡 < 0 into the LLM's residual stream while it processes an input user query.",
    "Evaluation of Expressed PreferencesWe ground our evaluation of the amount of expressed preference in the LLM's outputs using real-world human written data extracted from the Yelp Review Datasetfoot_6."
  ]
}